It is will be helpful for specific cases when you get options from other classes in DI or you build options in runtime in DI.  


### Describe the solution you'd like

I checked method AddRemoteSchema() and found that he use Configure method that can work with IServiceProvider:
``` 
private AuthenticationBuilder AddSchemeHelper<TOptions, [DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.PublicConstructors)] THandler>(string authenticationScheme, string? displayName, Action<TOptions>? configureOptions)
        where TOptions : AuthenticationSchemeOptions, new()
        where THandler : class, IAuthenticationHandler
{
  Services.Configure<AuthenticationOptions>(o =>
  {
    o.AddScheme(authenticationScheme, scheme =>
    {
       scheme.HandlerType = typeof(THandler);
       scheme.DisplayName = displayName;
    });
  });

  if (configureOptions != null)
  {
      Services.Configure(authenticationScheme, configureOptions);
  }

  Services.AddOptions<TOptions>(authenticationScheme).Validate(o =>
  {
      o.Validate(authenticationScheme);
      return true;
  });

  Services.AddTransient<THandler>();
  Services.TryAddEnumerable(ServiceDescriptor.Singleton<IPostConfigureOptions<TOptions>, PostConfigureAuthenticationSchemeOptions<TOptions>>());
  return this;
}
``` 

So my propose is adding new method overloading for AddSchemeHelper, like this:
``` 
private AuthenticationBuilder AddSchemeHelper<TOptions, [DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.PublicConstructors)] THandler, TConfigureDependency>(string authenticationScheme, string? displayName, Action<TOptions, TConfigureDependency> configureOptions)
   where TOptions : AuthenticationSchemeOptions, new()
   where THandler : class, IAuthenticationHandler
   where TConfigureDependency : class
 {
   Services.Configure<AuthenticationOptions>(o =>
   {
     o.AddScheme(authenticationScheme, scheme =>
     {
       scheme.HandlerType = typeof(THandler);
       scheme.DisplayName = displayName;
     });
   });

   var optionsBuilder = Services.AddOptions<TOptions>(authenticationScheme);

   optionsBuilder.Validate(o =>
   {
     o.Validate(authenticationScheme);
     return true;
   });
     
   optionsBuilder.Configure(configureOptions);

   Services.AddTransient<THandler>();
   Services.TryAddEnumerable(ServiceDescriptor.Singleton<IPostConfigureOptions<TOptions>, PostConfigureAuthenticationSchemeOptions<TOptions>>());
   return this;
 }
 ``` 
 
 Also adding new method overloading for AddScheme() like this:
 ``` 
 public virtual AuthenticationBuilder AddScheme<TOptions, [DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.PublicConstructors)] THandler, TConfigureDependency>(string authenticationScheme, string? displayName, Action<TOptions, TConfigureDependency> configureOptions)
    where TOptions : AuthenticationSchemeOptions, new()
    where THandler : AuthenticationHandler<TOptions>
    where TConfigureDependency : class
    => AddSchemeHelper<TOptions, THandler, TConfigureDependency>(authenticationScheme, displayName, configureOptions);
  ``` 
  
